cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG 

The paper deals with multimedia forensics, specifically the problem of device attribution for video sequences. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques to extract and match unique noise traces left by camera sensors on acquired images. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for matching fingerprints, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
